# Java Library Management Application

## Description

A simple library management REST API built with Java and Spring Boot. This project allows you to:

* Add new books
* Delete books by ID
* Update book information
* Search books by ID, title, author, and category
* Retrieve all books

## Technologies Used

* Java 17+
* Spring Boot
* Lombok

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone <your-repo-url>
   ```
2. Import the project into IntelliJ or your preferred IDE.
3. Build and run the project:

   ```bash
   mvn spring-boot:run
   ```
4. The application will start on `http://localhost:8080`

## API Endpoints

* `GET /books` - Get all books
* `POST /add` - Add a new book
* `DELETE /remove/{id}` - Delete a book by ID
* `PUT /update/{id}` - Update book by ID
* `GET /find/id/{id}` - Find book by ID
* `GET /find/title/{title}` - Find books by title
* `GET /find/author/{author}` - Find books by author
* `GET /find/category/{category}` - Find books by category

